There are differnet data types present in python like
1) int -----> integer
  Example
  11 is an inr
2) str -----> string
   Example
  "Hello" is a str
3) float 
   Example
   21.234 is a float


How to find a type of a value 
We use type() command which takes an argument
Example
Find type of 11, "Fruits", 1.3

print(type(11))
print(type("Fruits"))
print(type("1.3"))

Output
<class 'int'>
<class 'str'>
<class 'float'>


How to Convert
int ----> float
float(int)
Ex:
print(float(1))

Output
1.0

float ----> int  (Warning some data is lost)
int(float)
Ex:
print(int(1.2))

Output
1

str ----> int (If str doesnt contain int it will output error)
int(str)
ex:
print(str(1))

Output
"1"


int/float ----> str
str(int/float)
print(str(int/float))

Output
"int/float"

Boolean
1) 2 values
   i)True
  ii)False

int(True)
Output
1

int(False)
Output
0

bool(1)
Output
True


bool(0)
Output
False
